&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join a successful, vibrant and patient-focused Women’s Health Services Department at Whittington Health as a Locum Consultant in Obstetrics and Gynaecology with special interest in in lower urinary tract service (LUTS). &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will join the current medical staff in obstetrics and gynaecology and will contribute to the obstetrics and gynaecology rota based at the Whittington Hospital.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be expected to deliver clinical excellence and demonstrate a strong commitment to multi-professional working. A willingness to learn and work within a constantly changing environment is necessary together with the ability to remain calm under pressure.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;You will need to demonstrate how your skill mix will help the department thrive and develop.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Entry onto the GMC specialist register is essential. Please see job description for full person specification. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is fixed term maternity cover.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
